title: Short Story Collection Vol. 054
creator: Various
source: Librivox recording of a public-domain text
description: LibriVox’s Short Story Collection 054: a collection of 20 short works of fiction in the public domain read by a group of LibriVox members. This collecton comprises: Aunt Nell by George A. Birmingham (1865-1950) The Cat and Cupid by Arnold Bennett (1867-1931) Chu-Bu and Sheemish by Lord Dunsany (Edward J. M. D. Plunkett) (1878-1957) The District Doctor by Ivan S. Turgenev (1818-1883) The Eagle’s Nest by Bjørnstjerne Bjørnson (1832-1910) Trans: Rasmus Bjørn Anderson (1846–1936) The Indigent Brahman from Folk-Tales of Bengal by Lal Behari Day The Reverend Lal Behari Dey (Bengali: লাল বিহারী দে - also transliterated as Lal Behari Day) (1824–1892) The Missing Mortgagee by R. Austin Freeman (1862-1943) Oliver Twist, Chapter IX by Charles Dickens (1812-1870) The Pawnshop Keeper (from Futurist Stories) by Marjorie Verner-Reed (1894-?) A Respectable Woman by Kate Chopin (1850-1904) A Retrieved Reformation by O. Henry (1862-1910) The Slaughter of an Ox at Sea by Pierre Loti (1850-1923); trans. T.P. O’Connor M.P. (1848-1929) The Survivors by Elsie Singmaster Lewars (1879-1958) The Sword of Welleran by Lord Dunsany (Edward J. M. D. Plunkett) (1878-1957) The Undertaker's Chat by Mark Twain (1835-1910) Up the Slide by Jack London (1876-1916) The Upturned Face by Stephen Crane (1871-1900) War by Jack London (1876-1916) The Weight Of Obligation by Rex Beach (1877-1949) When Lincoln Licked A Bully by Irving Bacheller (1859-1940) For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording. For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org. M4B format available
